All of this gives me awful depression and anxiety. I’m not a very good partner, I’m always stuck in my head or trying to get out of it by distracting myself. It’s so hard. I can hardly describe it.

New ideas flood me. When I’m trying to do normal things, like sleep, work, and drive, it’s all I can do. I daydream of my story and the characters. They’re stuck in my head. But I’m stuck in the plot and I don’t want to write because my heart is hurting b

But I’m obsessive. That’s where things get hard. I can either do the thing on hyper focus and I do it very well, or I don’t know how to do the thing. I can’t sit and write things for my book in plain order: I think about what will happen in the end while I’m halfway done.

When a normal person sees a head of lettuce fall to the ground in the grocery store, they only think how they won’t buy that lettuce. For me, my head explodes with WHY. it’s incredible. I’m so creative, every passing thought needs to be considered.

Recently I am back at it, but it is so hard. I have thirteen or so story ideas that I’ve had officially. But as is a trait of adhd, every time I look at a thing a new possibility of a story is created.

SO LISTEN: I was a writer from the moment I could talk. I have been telling stories since I was a kid. I remember some of them. My mom knew that is what I’d be. But somewhere along the way, I realized how difficult it was and started to give up on that.
